<section xml:id="sec_first-intro" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Electrostatic Induction</title>

  <introduction>
    
     <p>
      A redistribution of charges in a neutral object when a charged object is brought 
      near it is called an electrostatic induction. Neighboring charges which are brought 
      near a neutral object are known as <em>inducing charges</em>, charges developed on a 
      neutral object are known as <em>induced charges</em>. Induced charges closer to 
      the inducing charges are known as <em>bound charges</em> and charges away from 
      inducing charges are known as <em>free charges</em> (<xref ref="fig2"/>). 
     </p>
